% references.bib — M4 Final Paper Bibliography
% Priority Inheritance Protocol — Seminar Paper
% Nnaemeka Nnachi-Egwu, Hochschule Hamm-Lippstadt
%
% ANNOTATION NOTES (for student reference management per seminar instructions,
% slide 2: "write for each related reference a short note of how it is related"):
% Stored as comments here to avoid rendering in the bibliography output.
%
% [Buttazzo2011] PRIMARY SOURCE. Chapter 7 (pp.205-249). All formal definitions,
%   lemmas, theorems, blocking formulas, and protocol comparison (Table 7.5).
% [Sha1990]      ORIGINAL PIP/PCP PAPER [SRL90]. Both PIP (§7.6) and PCP (§7.7)
%   introduced here. Theorem 7.2 and Lemmas 7.1-7.5 are due to these authors.
% [Kopetz2011]   REAL-TIME DEFINITION (physical instant). Course slides slide 7.
%   Grounds priority inversion as correctness failure, not performance issue.
% [Abella2015]   WCET TRUSTWORTHINESS. Buttazzo's B_i formula assumes exact
%   delta_{j,k} values; this paper shows WCET estimation is itself unreliable.
% [Gracioli2013] MULTIPROCESSOR SCOPE. Measures real OS overhead (IPI latency,
%   cache loss) missing from Buttazzo's uniprocessor B_i formula.
% [Behrmann2004] UPPAAL TUTORIAL. Timed automata syntax, guard/invariant/
%   sync/assignment labels, query language (A[], E<>). Used for pip_model.xml.
% [Baker1991]    SRP ORIGIN [Bak91]. Multi-unit resources, EDF, stack sharing.
%   Table 7.5 SRP row; distinguishes EDF-capable protocols from PIP.

